SOCIALLY MONOGAMOUS. That is the key word. It means they will form pair bonds, but Extra-pair mating is still rampant like it is in red foxes, african wild dogs, etc. Meaning that the fathers have a good chance of being cuckolds. This rarely happens in wolves in the wild (red, grey, timber), which are genetically monogamous. They are NOT cuckholds.

https://academic.oup.com/beheco/article/23/6/1186/189912
https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fevo.2019.00341/full (urban coyotes and swift foxes too, according to this)

Note: Ethiopian wolves are not actually wolves, they are foxes/coyote.
